Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on a complete mapping and localization system for a mobile robot in an urban environment. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper describes a novel pole detector algorithm for extracting landmarks from 3-D lidar data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques for pole detection. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper describes an intelligent system for long-term vehicle localization. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve natural language processing for describing the proposed system and its implementation.
